President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 9, 2012, as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. This day is dedicated to honoring the brave men and women who have served in the Armed Forces and have been held as prisoners of war. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices and hardships endured by these individuals, including physical torture and separation from loved ones. It calls upon all Americans to observe this day by honoring prisoners of war, service members, and veterans. The proclamation also encourages government officials and organizations to hold appropriate ceremonies and activities to commemorate this day.